[tool-call] delta {"path":"tests/src/org.apache.seata/seata-all/2.1.0/src/test/java/org_apache_seata/seata_all/TCCResourceManagerTest.java","edits":[{"oldText":"import java.lang.reflect.Method;\n\nimport org.apache.seata.core.exception.TransactionException;\n","newText":"import java.lang.reflect.Method;\n\nimport org.apache.seata.common.loader.EnhancedServiceLoader;\nimport org.apache.seata.config.ConfigurationFactory;\nimport org.apache.seata.core.exception.TransactionException;\n"},{"oldText":"public class TCCResourceManagerTest {\n    private static final String ACTION_NAME = \"sampleTccAction\";\n","newText":"public class TCCResourceManagerTest {\n    private static final String CONFIG_TYPE_PROPERTY = \"config.type\";\n    private static final String ACTION_NAME = \"sampleTccAction\";\n"},{"oldText":"    void setUpTccResource() throws NoSuchMethodException {\n        resourceManager = new TCCResourceManager();\n","newText":"    void setUpTccResource() throws NoSuchMethodException {\n        resetSeataConfiguration();\n        resourceManager = new TCCResourceManager();\n"},{"oldText":"    private static Method method(String name, Class<?>... parameterTypes) throws NoSuchMethodException {\n        return SampleTccAction.class.getMethod(name, parameterTypes);\n    }\n","newText":"    private static void resetSeataConfiguration() {\n        System.clearProperty(CONFIG_TYPE_PROPERTY);\n        EnhancedServiceLoader.unload(io.seata.config.ConfigurationProvider.class);\n        ConfigurationFactory.reload();\n    }\n\n    private static Method method(String name, Class<?>... parameterTypes) throws NoSuchMethodException {\n        return SampleTccAction.class.getMethod(name, parameterTypes);\n    }\n"}]}
[tool-call] end id=call_0WjOvv0EmwkMPp8sCsSDZGjc|fc_0770789330961eeb0169f16263ea148193ba4d409257adcec6 name=edit args={"path": "tests/src/org.apache.seata/seata-all/2.1.0/src/test/java/org_apache_seata/seata_all/TCCResourceManagerTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.lang.reflect.Method;\n\nimport org.apache.seata.core.exception.TransactionException;\n", "newText": "import java.lang.reflect.Method;\n\nimport org.apache.seata.common.loader.EnhancedServiceLoader;\nimport org.apache.seata.config.ConfigurationFactory;\nimport org.apache.seata.core.exception.TransactionException;\n"}, {"oldText": "public class TCCResourceManagerTest {\n    private static final String ACTION_NAME = \"sampleTccAction\";\n", "newText": "public class TCCResourceManagerTest {\n    private static final String CONFIG_TYPE_PROPERTY = \"config.type\";\n    private static final String ACTION_NAME = \"sampleTccAction\";\n"}, {"oldText": "    void setUpTccResource() throws NoSuchMethodException {\n        resourceManager = new TCCResourceManager();\n", "newText": "    void setUpTccResource() throws NoSuchMethodException {\n        resetSeataConfiguration();\n        resourceManager = new TCCResourceManager();\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static Method method(String name, Class<?>... parameterTypes) throws NoSuchMethodException {\n        return SampleTccAction.class.getMethod(name, parameterTypes);\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static void resetSeataConfiguration() {\n        System.clearProperty(CONFIG_TYPE_PROPERTY);\n        EnhancedServiceLoader.unload(io.seata.config.ConfigurationProvider.class);\n        ConfigurationFactory.reload();\n    }\n\n    private static Method method(String name, Class<?>... parameterTypes) throws NoSuchMethodException {\n        return SampleTccAction.class.getMethod(name, parameterTypes);\n    }\n"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating resource manager setup**\n\nI’m thinking about how our setup can clear system properties and reload before initializing a new TCCResourceManager. It seems that referencing ConfigurationFactory imports should be safe since it was already initialized from the previous test. Reloading might fix issues, keeping only the active class while using EnhancedServiceLoader unload. However, if the TCCResourceManager class has failed once, it won't work since it hasn't loaded before the setup line. I wonder if another test might trigger it, especially with TccRegisterResourceParser and DefaultResourceManager involved.\n\n**Considering git commits**\n\nIt looks like I need to create a commit after the generation step. Now, should I amend the existing commit or create a new one? Since I want to keep things clean, maybe making a new commit would be better. I might want to check the git log for context. But I also need to address unstaged or untracked changes in the metadata — I’ll have to modify the file accordingly. Let's plan this out!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0770789330961eeb0169f16253ee4881939fd773abe5b8c56c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8WJjiVvHVOnnQ1WH4nzEGsr1JXH8N7U5WzJid8UqDlx55bgl7ueNu09gt57-hMwLBYxLr3vY-3ahO-Y9UTr2iCOx-frDOK7Oun-8ym6iIV7cbdkfYmDJ3j83SMB_RiCr2LtiBwomse61vRcd2QY0AJa1ts7744CyhAtl7cnYLyHNi4IWhG0dwHMmOamJOP5rACHukGq9-k0O2sxgLbBUESYuiYYg93SWD5q5EBnvBVyK8ypaP7yOkzsXT2TbEXeKBQyMdHBtJQegTFqNrHM2N3QMJya0o3OtlqT-UaSCe9ykRSrznaySLJ4WZBFF3fgvikjOo_72sbtu_LzvKUs-hLK24p19isvrObjXR5artDhMno16_ssQIvT9WtzykvOdvC2C4XMAjdHdMp59IxFlEVjfCnObO8vRCEkYBPqndC7JbGZ1Vb9wjKoT3fNSdTk8psKh2f7KVk-1skKpqnSzJ0M4Q1SDR23tP9G7AMjdjx99Xju3NieAFnPNfKf_YbCqwOtpWkuRHl4GoHwE0QsH9B-m-ji0se8asFn0Q5ImIGtPEPzILUK2ye2OrLFxgFtpdIKh0N16b7jDyfFCjOhTIKf67DfiekzwZiUu2R9cpa2P0UIyfG1lRnoA0mqNsIip1hSxgKR4BHoAO79VfEnlawLeP7-lSyuWumI-bl5c4TeaGMMs4yBlLn