[assistant] Fixed the failure by resetting Seata’s global configuration state before `TCCResourceManager` is initialized in the new test.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - `ConfigurationFactoryInnerOldConfigurationInvocationHandlerTest` leaves `config.type=oldcompat` and a legacy configuration provider active.
[assistant] - `TCCResourceManager` extends `AbstractResourceManager`, whose static initializer reads Seata configuration.
[assistant] - When initialized after that previous test, Seata tried to call `getInt(String, Integer)` on the legacy test configuration and failed.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] - Updated `TCCResourceManagerTest` to clear `config.type`, unload the legacy `io.seata.config.ConfigurationProvider`, and reload `ConfigurationFactory` before creating `TCCResourceManager`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Commit amended:
[assistant] - `17d366b59 Add TCC resource manager dynamic access tests`
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run the Gradle test command locally.
