[assistant-event] text_start
[assistant] Fixed the reset logic.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause of the second failure:
[assistant] - I cleared `config.type` before touching `ConfigurationFactory`.
[assistant] - If `ConfigurationFactory` had not initialized yet, its static initializer then saw no `config.type` from `registry.conf` / system properties and failed with `config type can not be null`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] - `TCCResourceManagerTest` now resets Seata to file-based config before reloading:
[assistant]   - `config.type=file`
[assistant]   - `config.file.name=file.conf`
